Select the VPC on your services page
Click on launch VPC wizard
Click on create VPC. 
Enter the VPC name as private VPC, in IPV4 CIDR block as enter 10.0.0.0/24
In IPV6 CIDR block choose amazon provided IPV6 CIDR block
Click on create VPC
Then VPC will be successfully created
Open the subnet option
Then click on create a subnet.
Select the created VPC.
Name the subnet as per your convenience,
Check in the IPV6 only
In the IPV6 CIDR block in the second line there is space to enter a number, enter 04
Then click create a subnet.
Then go to the routing table,click create route table, enter the name, add the VPC that you have created. 
Then click on create router table.
Successfully connected  subnets to the routing table with a VPC.
Go to the internet gateway, click on create internet gateway.
Enter the name, then click on create internet gateway.
Right-click on the created internet gateway, click on attach to VPC
Select the VPC that you have created.
Then click on attach internet gateway


Output - Go to the Internet gateway page, show the subnet attached.




